If you're a fan of hot bars there is plenty to like here. Despite hit bars being a fairly terrible value for the money I am very thankful for hot bars due to my myriad of food restrictions. Hot bars give me the option of getting a little of this and a little of that and I enjoy the variety. There is a healthy variety of sandwiches and salads along with other refrigerated food stuffs to fill your belly and a tantalizing selection of chocolates to tickle your fancy. There are wines and a well-curated drink selection but if you're looking for ambiance you will have to create your own.

This is such a great little spot! You can pick as much or as little as you'd like, very much like Whole Foods in that way, except they have a much more eclectic, local vibe, clearly listing on their wall exactly how many local suppliers they're featuring that day as well as the name of those suppliers. They have a huge wine room as well as a great selection of local, organic wines. There is a small seating area that could be bigger, as well as a wine bar. The gluten free cheddar popovers are amazing, as well as the selection of organic teas and sodas. So many awesome little treats to make your own gift basket for coworkers or relatives. This is now our 'spot' in Chicago!
